Citation.sAbstract: Heat capacity for 1-butyl-3-methylimidazolium trifluoromethanesulfonate [C4mim]OTf in the  temperature range of (5 to 370) K has been measured in an adiabatic calorimeter. The temperature  Tfus = (290.98 +- 0.01) K and the enthalpy of fusion dfusHm = (19.32 +- 0.02) kJ*mol-1 were  determined. A solid-phase transition was observed near T = 120 K. Thermodynamic functions for the  compound in the condensed state were calculated. Trends in the solid-liquid phase change entropies,  OAtrSm, for 1-alkyl-3-methylimidazolium salts [Cnmim]An were analyzed. The increment to OAtrS was  shown to increase with n. It was found that OAtrSm = 66.4 +- 1.3 J.K-1.mol-1 for all the studied  [C4mim]An ionic liquids except [C4mim]NTf2. This difference can be partly explained by formation of  two distinguishable conformers of the NTf2- anion in the liquid state.
Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic properties of 1-butyl-3-methylimidazolium trifluoromethanesulfonate ionic  liquid in the condensed state
